- cs.PL (Programming Languages): The paper discusses errors in spreadsheets, which can be seen as a type of programming language. 
- cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction): The paper may be relevant to HCI researchers who study how people interact with spreadsheets and how errors can affect their work. 
- cs.CY (Computers and Society): The paper may be relevant to researchers who study the impact of spreadsheet errors on society, such as in financial or scientific contexts. 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security): While not directly related to cryptography or security, the paper may be relevant to researchers who study the security implications of spreadsheet errors in sensitive contexts.
